      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 105: The macOS-specific LOCAL_HOSTVARS assignment drops $(HOSTVARS), unlike the Android path. That means the vpx configure step can lose the contrib-provided compiler/binutils environment while adding ASFLAGS, which is especially risky for cross or non-default toolchain builds. Preserve HOSTVARS and append the macOS assembler flag instead.\n```suggestion\nLOCAL_HOSTVARS\u003d$(HOSTVARS) ASFLAGS\u003d\"-mmacosx-version-min\u003d$(MIN_OSX_VERSION)\"\n```",
      "revId": "4286ef98738832fcf35b5b4ea8386f65357261c9",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
    },
    {
