      "writtenOn": "2026-05-28T17:18:49Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 63: The new HAVE_MACOSX branch is placed before HAVE_IOS. If HAVE_MACOSX is also defined for iOS/Darwin-style builds in this contrib system, iOS will now take the macOS path and bypass the existing iOS-specific branch. Prefer checking HAVE_IOS first or combine the identical ASFLAGS configure path so iOS behavior cannot be accidentally shadowed.\n```suggestion\nifdef HAVE_IOS\n\tcd $\u003c \u0026\u0026 $(HOSTVARS) ASFLAGS\u003d\"$(CFLAGS)\" ./configure $(X264CONF)\nelse\nifdef HAVE_MACOSX\n\tcd $\u003c \u0026\u0026 $(HOSTVARS) ASFLAGS\u003d\"$(CFLAGS)\" ./configure $(X264CONF)\nelse\n\tcd $\u003c \u0026\u0026 $(HOSTVARS) ./configure $(X264CONF)\nendif\nendif\n```",
      "revId": "4286ef98738832fcf35b5b4ea8386f65357261c9",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
    }
